					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Each attribute byte affects an area of 32x32 pixels (except for the last row, which affects 32x16-pixel areas), which would be 4 "standard" metatiles (each one has the palette selected by 2 bits). So if you meant that 4 metatiles (or an equivalent area) changed colors, that's supposed to happen. In fact, this is the reason I suggested you update the attributes every 32 scrolled pixels while scanning 2 columns of metatiles. If you mean something else though, something really wrong is going on...!</div>

